{
  "texts": [
    "In fact, small language models (SLMs) that are fine-tuned for specific tasks often outperform more generalized large language models (Hao, 2025; Sejnowski, 2024).",
    "SLMs trained on low resource languages such Marathi, Malay, Turkish, Arabic are becoming common (Budur & Güngör, 2025; Chaudhari et al., 2024).",
    "Such models can help SLPs expand their services to a widening group of multilingual individuals.",
    "AI systems designed to carry out specific tasks are referred to as \"agentic AI,\" or simply \"agents.\"",
    "These agents operate using three key principles: prior knowledge from pre-training, task-specific intentionality, and their role as user proxies (Bandura, 2006)."
  ]
}